{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","heading_level":2,"sibling_index":1,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The optional grouping identifier variable --GRPID is Permissible in all domains that are based on the general observation classes.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"It is used to identify relationships between records within a USUBJID within a single domain (e.g., intervention records for a combination therapy where treatments in the combination varies from subject to subject).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In such cases, the relationship is defined by assigning the same unique character value to the --GRPID variable.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The values used for --GRPID can be any values the sponsor chooses; however, if the sponsor uses values with some embedded meaning (rather than arbitrary numbers), those values should be consistent across the submission to avoid confusion.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"It is important to note that --GRPID has no inherent meaning across subjects or across domains.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0428_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":428,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§8.1 Relating Groups of Records Within a Domain Using the --GRPID Variable","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Using --GRPID in the general-observation class domains can reduce the number of records in the RELREC, SUPP--, and CO datasets, when those datasets are submitted to describe relationships/associations for records or values to a \"group\" of general observation class records.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":["RELREC","SUPP--","CO"],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.1+","ts":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
